main event: A UFO sighting reported on 23 July 1954 in Bourne, Illinois, evaluated as a meteor.
interesting points: The sighting duration was noted as 2 minutes, believed possibly erroneous,Only one object was observed, which was described as falling,The object was light brown in color and resembled a rocket,It blinked on and off with a bright flash and had a bright flame with spots on its tail,There were 10-15 other observations during this incident.
sighted object: one light brown object resembling a rocket
witnesses: civilian observation reported to Air Force
